 bring together contested socioecological imaginaries, practices, and relations. Combining fieldwork and historical accounts, Saguin demonstrates how people—powerful and marginalized—interact with the state and the environment to produce the unequal landscapes of urbanization at and beyond the city's edge.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aHuman ecologyzPhilippines. 0aPolitical ecologyzPhilippineszManilay20th century. 0aPolitical ecologyzPhilippineszManilay21st century. 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishz978311099319608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022z9783110993134oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUIUC Life Sciences 2023 eBook packagez978311123611708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076649340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520382671?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520382671423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520382671/original  a978-3-11-076649-3  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099319-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-123611-7  UIUC Life Sciences 2023 eBook packageb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DPMb2022